# Final code quality audit (delegate to skill)

Before treating a coding task as **complete** for changes under `src/` (or when the user asks for a standards check):

1. **Read** the project skill at `.cursor/skills/algotrading-code-quality/SKILL.md` and apply its workflow (PhD-level rigor, **SOLID**, **composition over inheritance**, checklist, output template).
2. **Treat** `documentation/code_standards.md` as the authoritative standard; the skill summarizes it but does not replace it.
3. When appropriate, run **`make check`** from the repo root and fold results into the audit.

Skip the full audit only for trivial edits (e.g. typo-only) or when the user explicitly opts out.
